        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 3:54PM CDT by NWS Jackson MS</headline>
        <description>At 354 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Afton, or 13 miles south of Tallulah, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southeastern
Madison Parish in northeastern Louisiana and southwestern Warren
Counties, including the following locations... Delta.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 PM CDT for
northeastern Louisiana...and west central Mississippi.</instruction>
